---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"Blanc Browser Features — Minimal browsing, built in"}
  description={"Explore search built into the Blanc Island, plus ad and tracker blocking, private tabs, the command palette, tab groups, and the security architecture of a minimal desktop browser."}
  path="/features"
  page="features"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"Search, tabs, and browser controls in one floating Island, with built-in blocking, private tabs, tab groups, and structural security."}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Features", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/features" }
  ]
}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-hub-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">features</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--hub" aria-labelledby="features-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">the browser, reduced</p>
    <h1 id="features-title">Less browser. More of what you opened it for.</h1>
    <p>Blanc keeps the everyday browser tools close without building a dashboard around them — and ships no AI assistant hovering over any of it. Choose the part of your session you want to make quieter.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-hub-list" aria-label="Blanc browser features">
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="island">
      <p class="feature-number">01</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">the blanc island</p>
        <h2>One small control surface. The whole browser.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Search, tabs, navigation, the current site, and page controls live together, so the page stays in front.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/island" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="island" data-cta-position="feature-hub">Meet the Island <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row feature-hub-row--featured" id="ad-blocking">
      <p class="feature-number">02</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">built in</p>
        <h2>Fewer ads. Less tracking. No extension required.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Blanc includes ad and tracker blocking at the browser level, with a quiet per-page count and an option for sites you choose to allow.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/ad-blocking" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="ad-blocking" data-cta-position="feature-hub">How blocking works <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="private-tabs">
      <p class="feature-number">03</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">a clean trail</p>
        <h2>Private tabs that stay out of the record.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Private pages do not enter Blanc history, session restore, or reopen-closed. Close the private chip when you are finished.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/private-tabs" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="private-tabs" data-cta-position="feature-hub">Read about private tabs <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="commands">
      <p class="feature-number">04</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">keyboard first</p>
        <h2>One shortcut to move through your whole session.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Command or Control L blends open tabs, favorites, history, and named groups with live suggestions from your chosen search engine. Type / to run a browser command.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/command-palette" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="command-palette" data-cta-position="feature-hub">Explore commands <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="tab-groups">
      <p class="feature-number">05</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">a little order</p>
        <h2>Keep the tabs you need. Tuck away the rest.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Name a group for the task in front of you. Blanc keeps the active one on the Island while the rest stay close, not constantly visible.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/tab-groups" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="tab-groups" data-cta-position="feature-hub">Explore tab groups <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="sync">
      <p class="feature-number">06</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">pick up anywhere</p>
        <h2>Your open tabs, on your other devices.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Opt in per device and Blanc shares what each machine has open — end-to-end encrypted, read-only, and never a merged live session.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/sync" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="sync" data-cta-position="feature-hub">How tab sync works <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-hub-row" id="security">
      <p class="feature-number">07</p>
      <div>
        <p class="feature-label">private by architecture</p>
        <h2>Security that is structural, not bolted on.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-row-end">
        <p>Sandboxed pages, network-level blocking, end-to-end encrypted sync, and a usage ping you can switch off. The quiet parts, documented.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/features/security" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="security" data-cta-position="feature-hub">Read the security story <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="feature-close-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">ready when you are</p>
    <h2 id="feature-close-title">A quieter browser is a small download away.</h2>
    <a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="feature-hub" data-cta-position="feature-hub-close">choose your download</a>
  </section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
